---
name: setup-env
description: Provision the client/server development environment, VS Code extensions, and workspace settings from requirements.md.
inputs:
  target:
    description: client, server, extensions, verify, or all
    default: all
  installOpenCvNative:
    description: On Windows server, optionally install OpenCV native libraries through vcpkg.
    default: false
---

# setup-env.agent

## Goal

Create a reproducible development setup from [requirements.md](/home/kosta/clientT-1/requirements.md):

- Client: Ubuntu/WSL2, C++, CMake, g++, gdb, OpenCV, Qt, Google Test, vcpkg, Docker
- Server: Windows, Java, Gradle, Spring, Docker, optional OpenCV native toolchain
- IDE: VS Code extensions and workspace settings aligned to both stacks

## Execution Rules

1. Read [requirements.md](/home/kosta/clientT-1/requirements.md) before making environment changes.
2. Use the workspace scripts under `skills/scripts` instead of embedding package-manager commands inline.
3. Prefer the target-specific entrypoints:
   - Linux or WSL2 client: `bash skills/scripts/setup-env.sh client`
  - Linux or WSL2 vcpkg only: `bash skills/scripts/setup-env.sh vcpkg`
   - Linux or WSL2 extensions only: `bash skills/scripts/setup-env.sh extensions`
   - Linux or WSL2 full setup: `bash skills/scripts/setup-env.sh all`
   - Windows server: `pwsh -File skills/scripts/setup-env.ps1 -Target server`
   - Windows server with optional native OpenCV: `pwsh -File skills/scripts/setup-env.ps1 -Target server -InstallOpenCvNative`
4. After installation, run the matching verify command:
   - Linux or WSL2: `bash skills/scripts/setup-env.sh verify`
   - Windows: `pwsh -File skills/scripts/setup-env.ps1 -Target verify`

## What To Install

### Client Toolchain

- Build tools: CMake, Ninja, g++, make, pkg-config
- Debugging: gdb
- UI and vision: Qt 6, OpenCV
- Test: Google Test
- Package and deployment: vcpkg, Docker

### Server Toolchain

- Java runtime and build: OpenJDK 21, Gradle
- IDE and tooling: IntelliJ IDEA Community, VS Code, Git
- Deployment: Docker Desktop
- Optional native support: CMake, Visual Studio Build Tools, vcpkg, OpenCV

### VS Code

- C/C++, CMake Tools, Docker, Java Pack, Spring Boot support, Gradle support
- GitHub Copilot and Copilot Chat
- Workspace recommendations in [.vscode/extensions.json](/home/kosta/clientT-1/.vscode/extensions.json)
- Shared settings in [.vscode/settings.json](/home/kosta/clientT-1/.vscode/settings.json)

## Verification

- Client verification checks `cmake`, `g++`, `gdb`, `docker`, `pkg-config`, Qt 6, OpenCV, and vcpkg.
- Server verification checks `java`, `gradle`, `git`, and optional native toolchain components.

## Notes

- The fixed RTSP endpoint contract stays in [interface-protocol.md](/home/kosta/clientT-1/interface-protocol.md); this agent only provisions development tools.
- Docker post-install group membership may still require sign-out/sign-in on Linux.
- Native OpenCV on Windows is optional because some Java stacks package it with Gradle dependencies instead of a machine-wide install.